HOW TO USE SCRIPT FILES
Author: Trong-Dat Nguyen
==========================================

const.sh is the global file included by other sh files. It contains consts for all scripts

To use a copy database from another location and execute the database:
./run_single.sh


To start the mongodb 
./start_server.sh <cache_size>
cache_size: 0 ~ max_DRAM_size 

To stop the server
./stop_server.sh

To get the statistics information for a running mongodb server:
./get_coll_stats.sh <out_dir>
You can specify any desired output dir as out_dir


